out the politics of knowledge production and the tensions between working-class intellectuals and the state.Duke University Press Scholars of Color First Book Award recipient  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 10. Jan 2022) 0aIntellectualszPuerto RicoxAttitudes. 0aLabor movementzPuerto RicoxHistoryy20th century. 0aPress and politicszPuerto RicoxHistoryy20th century. 0aPress, LaborzPuerto RicoxHistoryy20th century. 0aWorking classxPolitical activityzPuerto RicoxHistoryy20th century. 7aHISTORY / Latin America / General.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781478022091zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478022091423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781478022091/original  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles